        "Spend" .

oc:kn_86325fb5 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Ongoing campaign management" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Weekly optimization cycle: review search terms for negatives → check Quality Scores <6 → pause low CTR ads → adjust bids for high performers. Monthly: competitor analysis, landing page review, audience refresh, budget reallocation" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Regular optimization prevents budget decay and captures new opportunities as search landscapes shift" .

oc:kn_9d4c2b53 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When conducting keyword research" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Gather seed keywords from product terms, competitor ads, customer language, support tickets. 2. Expand with Google Keyword Planner (filter by volume/CPC/competition). 3. Group by theme/intent into ad groups (15-20 keywords max). 4. Assign match types (exact for high-intent, phrase for balance, broad for discovery). 5. Build negative keyword lists at account, campaign, and ad group levels." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_a5f36edf a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before launching any new campaign" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before campaign launch: verify conversion tracking is enabled, landing pages are live and mobile-optimized, negative keyword lists are populated, and budget/bidding strategy align with goals" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing tracking or broken landing pages make performance data unreliable and waste spend" .

oc:kn_e1ce7498 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building account hierarchy from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Structure accounts with 4 campaign types: Brand, Non-Brand Search, Competitor, and Performance Max — each with themed ad groups containing 15-20 keywords max" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Proper segmentation enables independent budget control, bidding strategies, and performance measurement per campaign intent" .

